250 g Ground Pork
1 unit(s) Yellow Onion
1 unit(s) Green Bell Pepper
8 g Enchilada Spice Blend
1 unit(s) Tomato
56 g Baby Spinach
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
1 cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
4 tbsp Ranch Dressing
4 g Garlic Salt
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.
Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch slices.
Peel, then cut onion into 1/4-inch pieces.
Halve tomatoes lengthwise, then thinly slice into half-moons.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high. When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then pork, onions and peppers. Cook for 4-5 min, breaking up pork into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.**
Season with Enchilada Spice Blend, garlic salt and pepper. Cook for 30 sec, stirring often, until fragrant.
Sprinkle with cheese. Remove from heat.

To large bowl, add spinach, tomatoes and ranch dressing. Season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat.

Just before serving, wrap tortillas in paper towels.
Microwave for 30 sec-1 min, until tortillas are warm and flexible. (TIP: You can skip this step if you don't want to warm the tortillas.)

Divide tortillas between plates.
Top with pork filling. Roll up tortillas.
Serve salad alongside.